In her remarks at Fort Carson in Colorado Springs, Second Lady Karen Pence thanked military spouses for their service and sacrifices. She also highlighted the Trump administration's efforts to support military spouses, including initiatives to improve employment opportunities and address licensing requirements for military spouses who frequently move. Pence also discussed the "With You All the Way! Dealing with Deployment" Comfort Kits that were being distributed to children with deployed parents from Fort Carson. She expressed her admiration for military spouses and their contributions to the armed forces and communities.